description:
&lt;p&gt;16.5 hours per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Health Care Assistant to join our friendly North West Community Nursing team. We are looking for a caring, motivated and adaptable person to join our busy, professional and dynamic team. You should display a commitment to interdisciplinary team working and strive to deliver excellent standards of care to people in their own environment. You will be able to demonstrate a real enthusiasm for community nursing, as well as a desire for on-going professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to travel independently across the region to fulfil the requirements of the post is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a permanent part time post of 16.5 hours a week working 8.30-14:00hrs over 3 days.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information please contact Team leader Jayne Richards on 01691 663609 or jayne.richards@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date: 17.11.2020 at Oswestry Health Centre SY11 1GA&lt;/p&gt;
